PART TWO — AIMING IT AT THE STRAIN (a SEPARATE problem, using SEPARATE data)
=====================================================================
The Codex teaches alchemy; it says nothing about the Forelhost Strain. For the cure,
Ismara works from two other inputs she has in hand: Antoine's documented Strain-1.0 data,
and the live patient (Davinia herself).

WHAT IS ACTUALLY KNOWN ABOUT STRAIN 1.0 (Antoine's Journal 1 — the ONLY documentation):
  - Engineered pathogen, deployed in Riften via the mead vats. ~73% transmission; ~89%
    lethality untreated within 14 days.
  - IT IS ACCELERATED BY RESTORATION. Healing magic does not cure it — it speeds its
    reproduction (lethality rose to ~94% WITH Restoration treatment). So Restoration is
    the one thing you must NOT pour into an infected body. Davinia — a Restoration-soaked
    Crown-host — is therefore an ideal victim, and a temple healer's instinct is exactly
    wrong here.
  - Antoine logged incubation, symptom progression, immune-response curves, and
    "Restoration interaction coefficients." That is the extent of the notation. There is
    no documented self-propagation, no "cure-kills-curer" — those are Strain 2.0 DESIGN
    GOALS Antoine had not built (and 2.0 does not exist). Do NOT import them.

THE ONE CURE THAT IS KNOWN TO WORK: Danica's. She purified an advanced case (Hemming)
  by offering her own life-force as the catalytic reagent — NOT standard Restoration —
  at a cost of roughly fifteen years of her life. It works, and it is brutal, and it
  burns Danica. The cure-project's whole POINT is to find an ALCHEMICAL cure that does
  not require spending Danica.

HOW ISMARA WOULD APPROACH IT (the research, not a solved answer — let play find the cure):
  - READ THE ENEMY: the Sight lets her watch the Strain move in Davinia's own blood
    (no one else can see it); Antoine's Journal 1 gives the interaction coefficients.
  - THE OBVIOUS FIRST HYPOTHESIS, by the law of opposition: the Strain thrives on VITALIS
    (it eats healing), so the natural line of inquiry is its opposite — a controlled
    VENITAS / entropic agent aimed at the PATHOGEN, not the host. This is a DIRECTION to
    test, not the confirmed cure; whether it pans out (and what it costs) is the GM's /
    the table's to determine.
  - THE COLLABORATOR: ALFONSO is the living master of VENITAS (Peryite's ordered decay).
    His role is AIM — keeping any entropic agent from simply poisoning Davinia. Her rigor,
    his fluency.
  - THE BENCHMARK: Saijah's Hircine gift BURNED the Strain out of her in a day. Study why
    — a working purge in miniature, and a clue to what the Strain cannot feed on or outrun.
  - STAGE IT: read the enemy -> form the hypothesis -> brew the agent (with Alfonso's aim)
    -> test against the benchmark -> refine. Real work, real near-misses; the cure is
    Davinia's lifeline and every session Ismara is the one who can deliver it is a session
    the player chooses her.

